<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-07T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="595" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1140/119: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-07T17:00:00-05:00">January 7, 1919—5 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>6881. For Davis from Rathbone. Treasury 687. Mission’s 154, January 4, 6 p.m.
                        Yours unnumbered to Secretary. All applications for loans concerning relief
                        should receive your consideration and study. You are expected to discuss the
                        same and to make recommendations to the Treasury.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>